{"info": {"author": "Avalon Parton", "author_email": "avalonlee@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# Multiwall\n\nSet your background on multiple monitors to random images from [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/), [mikedrawsdota](http://wallpapers.mikedrawsdota.com/#_=_), and more.\n\n## Installation\n\n```powershell\npy -3 -m pip install multiwall\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```powershell\npy -3 -m multiwall\n```\n\nThe default source is [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/), use the `--source` flag to change it.\n\n```powershell\npy -3 -m multiwall --source 'mikedrawsdota'\n```\n\n### As a Desktop Shortcut\n\n1. Create a file `wallpaper.pyw` with the following contents:\n\n    ```python\n    import multiwall\n    multiwall.main()\n    ```\n\n1. Set it to Open With `\"C:\\Windows\\pyw.exe\"`\n\n## Examples\n\n```powershell\n# 4k monitor + 1080p monitor (5760x2160 picture)\npy -3 -m multiwall --monitors \"3440x1440,1920x1080\"\n```\n\n![5760x2160](https://i.imgur.com/huusFe8.jpg)\n\n\n```powershell\n# 4k monitor + portait monitor\npy -3 -m multiwall --monitors \"3440x1440,1440x2560\"\n```\n![3440x1440,1440x2560](https://i.imgur.com/aNE8aYF.jpg)\n\n\n## Planned Features\n\n* [*] Automatic monitor size detection\n* [*] Custom search parameters\n* [*] Save images without setting wallpaper\n* [ ] Favorite images\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/avalonparton/multiwall", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "multiwall", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/multiwall/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/multiwall/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://gitlab.com/avalonparton/multiwall"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/multiwall/1.3/", "requires_dist": ["Pillow", "python-unsplash", "screeninfo"], "requires_python": 